@@BuildPathName
<TITLE BuildPathName function>
Summary
  Takes a directory (pathname) and a filename and puts them together to make a filename.
Description
  Appends PathName + FileName, and places a backslash between them, only if necessary. This is a useful
  function because PathName may or may end in a backslash, and FileName may or may not begin with a
  backslash.
Parameters
  PathName - A path name for the fully qualified filename you are creating (For example, 'C:\')
  FileName - A filename (For example, 'autoexec.bat')

